# Decide the Work-State Pass Shape

## Step

With ingress facts in hand, grill Joel to settle the pass:

- **Trigger**: hourly Inngest cron vs joining the existing observer tick
  (stream-observation) — one durable machine, not two.
- **Input**: live Slack read (board-style, truth) vs the ingested
  `channel_messages` stream (cheaper, but only as fresh as ingress) — or
  read ingested, verify live before waking.
- **Scope**: channel allowlist (cc-matt-p first; what else, if anything).
- **Findings + thresholds**: what counts as a "request" root; untagged-for-N-hours
  nudge threshold; :shitrat:-without-✅-for-N-days staleness threshold.
- **Emission**: observation page schema (provenance: permalink, root ts,
  work-state, thresholds crossed) + dispatcher wake payload, per
  wake-dont-feed; who gets woken.
- **Observability**: the per-stage receipts + funnel/trace command the launch
  gate demands, asserted at first enable (live-remainders-must-block).
- **Authorization**: the resolution states whether the build step is
  authorized and what its done-condition is.

## Result (2026-07-17)

Grilled with Joel this session; all calls his.

- **Trigger**: dedicated Inngest cron function on the system-bus worker, hourly. Not the observer tick, not a curator-style self-rescheduling beat.
- **Input**: the **live sweep is the candidate source** — one bounded `conversations.history` read per allowlisted channel per run (board semantics, root reactions authoritative). The ingested `channel_messages` feed is a prefilter/hint between runs, never the boundary of what exists (Matt's CMS-token root proved the feed can hole). Feed repairs are non-blocking.
- **Scope**: #cc-matt-p (C0211NSK3TP) + #brain-joel at launch; the allowlist is config, growth is a config change plus a decision note.
- **Request definition**: a thread root authored by a human other than Joel (bots excluded) — in cc-matt-p that is exactly Matt's roots; Joel's own roots are never findings.
- **Thresholds** (config-tunable starting values): untagged > 4 hours → finding; `:shitrat:` without ✅ > 7 days → stale finding.
- **Emission**: one observation page per run that has findings (items: permalink, author, work-state, age, thresholds crossed, provenance). Dispatcher wake fires only when an item's state/threshold is NEW since last notify — the pass keeps a small notified-state file as notification hygiene, never truth (Slack stays canonical). Dispatcher classifies per wake-dont-feed; default route joelclaw notify DM.
- **Observability** (launch gate): per-stage OTEL receipts (component `work-state-pass`) + one funnel command showing the last run (channels scanned, roots seen, findings, pages, wakes). Enable requires the seeded scenario (untagged root + stale started) to produce page + wake end-to-end, asserted live — verify runs, not registration (Inngest dead-binding lesson).
- **Feed repairs**: reaction-tap webhook-mode bug and ingress reconciliation are chartered as steps in [stream-observation](../stream-observation/stream-observation-brief.svx), referencing [the coverage asset](./slack-ingress-coverage-2026-07-17.svx); this effort does not block on them.
- **Authorization**: [Build the Work-State Pass](./build-work-state-pass.svx) is authorized with this resolution as its spec (Joel, 2026-07-17).
